There's no panacea in abstractions, they all leak eventually. Even if you just happen to be the unlucky bastard struck by odd cosmic rays.
And if you really know C you must *at least* have an idea of how the underlying machine works, and cannot be afraid to drop to that level.
If you find weird behaviour in Python/Ruby/whatever and want to debug it you *must* know C or C++.
I'll have to drop down to assembly to debug this one. This is exactly why I claim that a real dev understands *all* layers of abstraction.
